solution:
We apply the distributive property to get\begin{align*}
\frac{1}{4}\left(\frac{4}{y}+4y\right)&= \frac{1}{4}\cdot\frac{4}{y}+\frac{1}{4}\cdot 4y\\
&= \boxed{\frac{1}{y} + y}.
\end{align*}

