draw(Circle(O,1));

label("$O$",O,SE);

label("$P$",P,NW);

//label("$A$",A,SE);

label("$D$",D,S);

[/asy]

Triangle $POD$ is a 45-45-90 triangle, so $DO = DP = \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}$.  Therefore, the coordinates of $P$ are $\left(-\frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}, \frac{\sqrt{2}}{2}\right)$, so \[\tan 135^\circ = \frac{\sin 135^\circ}{\cos 135^\circ} = \frac{\sqrt{2}/2}{-\sqrt{2}/2} = \boxed{-1}.\]

Let $P$ be the point on the unit circle that is $240^\circ$ counterclockwise from $(1,0)$, and let $D$ be the foot of the altitude from $P$ to the $x$-axis, as shown below.

