Then $\tan \angle BAD = \frac{2}{x}$ and $\tan \angle CAD = \frac{3}{x}.$

We know that $\angle BAC = 45^\circ.$  By the tangent addition formula,
\begin{align*}
\tan \angle BAC &= \tan (\angle BAD + \angle CAD) \\
&= \frac{\tan \angle BAD + \tan \angle CAD}{1 - \tan \angle BAD \tan \angle CAD} \\
&= \frac{2/x + 3/x}{1 - 2/x \cdot 3/x} \\
&= \frac{5x}{x^2 - 6}.
\end{align*}Then $5x = x^2 - 6,$ or $x^2 - 5x - 6 = 0.$  This factors as $(x - 6)(x + 1) = 0,$  so $x = 6.$  The area of triangle $ABC$ is then $\frac{1}{2} \cdot 6 \cdot 5 = \boxed{15}.$

